<title type="html"><![CDATA[Toggle Image or Video Folder Thumbnails button]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=3196&amp;p=15011#p15011"><![CDATA[
Microsoft Windows 7 doesn't allow us to toggle thumbnails for a folder.<br /><br />I want them off most of the time for performance.<br /><br />Occasionally I want them on.<br /><br />I could live with a per folder setting.<br /><br />I absolutely do not want thumbnails on by default.<br />and sometimes I want them in folders that I didn't want it on earlier <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_e_surprised.gif" alt=":o" title="Surprised" /><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4518">AaronPeterson</a> — Thu Sep 25, 2014 11:44 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
